The TDD exercise is complete. All 6 tests pass:

1. Empty grid → empty grid
2. Single cell dies (underpopulation)
3. Two cells with 1 neighbor each die (underpopulation)
4. 2×2 block survives unchanged (still life)
5. Blinker oscillates vertical → horizontal
6. Dead cell with 3 live neighbors is born (reproduction)

The final implementation in `src/game-of-life.ts` has four focused functions: `isAlive`, `neighborCount`, `deadNeighbors`, and `nextGeneration`, using a sparse cell representation with `[number, number]` coordinates supporting infinite/negative grids.
